cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.FL, cs.SE 

This paper deals with the decidability of Separation Logic with recursively defined predicates, which is a topic related to logic and programming languages (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the use of Separation Logic for describing data structures such as trees and lists (cs.PL, cs.DS), and the decidability results are obtained by reduction to Monadic Second Order Logic on graphs with bounded tree width (cs.FL, cs.SE).
